# gjoa-patch:
#   baseline-firefox: 152.0
#   touches:
#     - servo/components/style/properties/computed_value_flags.rs
#     - servo/components/style/style_adjuster.rs
#     - layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp
#
gjoa dark mode — image-backed "island" detection + dark scrim (sibling to 0009).

A full-bleed raster background-image (a hero photo) with authored light text was
broken by the blanket luminance inversion: the text flipped to near-black over the
untouched dark image. This makes the engine backdrop-aware where bg meets fg.

- computed_value_flags.rs: new INHERITED bit SELF_OR_ANCESTOR_HAS_IMAGE_BACKDROP,
  propagated to a hero's descendants.
- style_adjuster.rs (set_bits): sets it for elements establishing a full-bleed
  RASTER hero (url()/image-set + cover/contain + non-tiled). Gradients, tiled
  textures, and decorative images are excluded.
- specified/color.rs: the foreground-inversion hook PRESERVES an inherited color
  (color/text-shadow/border-color) under an image backdrop so authored light text
  stays light; reset background-color still inverts (solid bgs go dark).
- nsDisplayList.cpp: paints a translucent dark scrim (gjoa.darkmode.scrim.alpha,
  default 140) over a hero's bg images, below content, so text reads on the photo.
